sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1475004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Cons. promoter, RBS, TetR and a double terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device will produce the TetR protein (Part:BBa_K1475003) using a constitutive promoter (Part:BBa_J23106) and RBS (Part:BBa_B0030) followed by a small artificial terminator (Part:BBa_B1002).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Weltz Pedersen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haiyao Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be less effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 6 residues.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1475003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains the coding sequence of the TetR protein. TetR binds to the pTet promoter and represses transcription. aTc (anhydrotetracycline) bind to the TetR protein and inhibits the function of TetR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Weltz Pedersen
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was constructed from the tetracycline repressor from transposon Tn10 (+LVA) (Part:BBa_C0040) using primers to remove the LVA protein digestion tag. That is THIS PART DOES NOT CONTAIN THE LVA PROTEIN DIGESTION TAG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Skrive hvilke primere der er brugt.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
